A majority of Americans disapprove ofthe way Ronald Reagan has handled the presidency and one-thirdbelieve he should resign, a new poll said.    The poll conducted by Newsweek magazine said 53 pct of therespondents gave Reagan a negative performance rating, nearlydouble his disapproval rating before the Iran/Contra scandal.    The magazine said, however, that Reagan remained personallypopular. By better than a three-to-one ratio, a majority ofthose polled said they liked Reagan on a personal level.    And Newsweek said 52 per cent of those questioned believedthe administration"s accomplishments outweighed its failures. REUTER&#3;